/1958-06-05/ed-1/", "word_coordinates": "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service"}], "segment_id": "/service/ndnp/fu/batch_fu_greenville_ver01/data/sn95047212/00529042334/1958060501/0110.xml", "segments": [{"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/resource/sn95047212/1958-06-05/ed-1/?sp=2"], "batch": ["fu_greenville_ver01"], "campaigns": [], "composite_location": ["0/united states/", "1/united states/florida/", "2/united states/florida/dade/", "3/united states/florida/dade/miami/"], "contributor": ["university of florida"], "date": "1958-06-05", "dates": ["1958-06-05"], "description": ["Page 2 Hata Citizen A GENERAL NEWSPAPER DEVOTED TO THE BEST INTERESTS OF ORGANIZED LABOR Published Every Thursday by The LABOR PRESS Inc Charles F Towle President P O Box 828 Phone PL 75031 Advertising Rates on Request Subscription Rate 1200 Per Year Entered as secondclass postal matter October 1 1920 at the Post Office at Miami Fla under Act of Congress of March 3 1879 CHAS F TOWLE Editor Official Organ of DADE COUNTY FEDERATION OF LABOR MIAMI BUILD ING TRADES COUNCIL FLORIDA STATE FEDERATED LABOR COUNCIL CITIZEN ADVISORY COMMITTEE Educational Committee of the Dade County Federation of Labor IPere it not for the labor press the labor movement would not be what it is today and any man who tries to injure a labor paper is a traitor to the cause SAMUEL GOMPERS America The Taser Two major antirecession weapons have fallen by the political wayside the victims of a doubtful coalition be tween a Republican Administration and a Congress con trolled by the GOP and conservative Democrats In the face of a 10monthold recession the nations worst since the end of World War 11 the White House and the Democratic leadership in Congress have teamed up to"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-01-27T17:02:00.860Z", "group": ["ndnp/fu", "university-of-florida-awardee"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/resource/sn95047212/1958-06-05/ed-1/?sp=2